We, at Saahas, recognise that the keys to running a successful NGO are transparency, authenticity & accountability.🌸🧿

We have always tried to maintain authenticity and vulnerability through our social media which is to this day handled only by the founder. 
Although we have maintained complete transparency in the process of receiving donations and managing our finances, we are taking it a step forward. We believe that transparency is needed to create trust and hence this new step. 

Everyone that donates, will henceforth be provided with a official receipt from the organisation. We will need to know your Name & Contact number for the same, which are to be sent (whatsapp) on the following number 8459592034!Given are the official donation details of Saahas. 👇

We have always been grateful for the abundant love, support and help. You make us what we are.❤️
Visits to see our work in person, are always welcome.
Remember, no donation is small.
“It’s not how much we give, but how much love we put into giving”
Thankyou again🙏

latestPosts.caption:
Treating animals is a rewarding job. Yes, there are a lot of struggles like finances, lack of work-life balance or lack of days off because the sickness doesn’t look at festivals but it’s a job that can make you feel satisfied. 

When each one of us go home at the end of the day, we feel satisfied that we’ve done something to make this world a better and a kinder place. 

If you like our work, please come and volunteer with us or donate to us on 8459592034 💓 Sukoon milega, karke dekho 💓

Today a case was reported to us about a pregnant dog who had fallen in a pit like structure close to a construction site and was not able to come out of there. 

When we reached there, we found out that she was probably there for some days. We managed to remove her out of the pit. 

And she’s now safe. She has a feeder who feeds her regularly. She has reached out to us for her. She’s going to take care of her till she delivers and post her delivery, Saahas will sterilise her. 

If you believe in our cause and our work, please donate to us on 8459592034 ♥️

latestPosts.caption:
Yesterday on her way back home, our founder saw a dead mother lying by road side and her puppy was standing beside her. 

When we saw the video, we felt really bad. When road accidents happen, the most basic decency people should have is to take the concerned animal to the vet and see around if there’s any help they can get. 

In this particular case, it felt like no one even fed the little puppy any food. He was absolutely malnourished. A puppy that age probably doesn’t know how to fend for his own food. 

These are the things that we need to change in the coming year. We need to be more responsible for the lives around us. These animals help us keep the streets safe and the pests away. We need to care for them. 

If you believe in our cause of helping animals, please donate to us on 8459592034 ♥️

Christmas is here and while some of you are lucky to be warm and safe, a lot of our animals are not. 

So why don’t we all celebrate for them as well? We’ve been celebrating secret santa at our offices but how about we celebrate it once for different shelter dogs and sponsor their food and care for one month? 

This Christmas, adopt our shelter dogs virtually and be their secret santa! Gift them a month of love and livelihood 🥹 

You can DM us or text us on 845952034 to know more about our virtual adoptions.

This beautiful female young adult was admitted with us two days ago with a really bad wound on her hind leg. Her leg has gone quite bad but we are going to try and save her leg with regular dressing and care. 

She is also weak and is currently on antibiotics, anti inflammatories and supplements. We have sent her blood work for analysis and will decide the further course of action in due time. 

If you wish to help us save Avni’s leg, please donate to us on 8459592034 ♥️♥️

latestPosts.caption:
Lisa was abandoned at our shelter almost 2 months ago with a severe skin infection. We believe that that’s why she was abandoned. 

She barely had any hair, had scabs all over her body and was very itchy. What happened with her was very sad. 

This is her after two months. She went through treatment and veterinarian diets and is now completely okay. She’s a very timid dog but friendly at the same time. 

We are urgently looking for someone to either foster her or adopt her. If you’re interested, please reach out to us on 8459592034 or DM us ♥️

We don’t know if we can save them, but they deserve a fighting chance. Right now, our priority is to raise funds for their X-rays and primary treatment.🙏🏻

Your kindness can be their lifeline. Please come forward and donate to help these little souls get the care they desperately need. Every contribution counts. 🙏
